<h2>

  <a name="recherchemoeglichkeiten"></a>



    Which search options are available?

  </h2>




<p>There are six categories providing structured access to the interviews:</p>
<p>· Name: Name of the Interviewee</p>
<p>· Group: Persecuted Group the Interviewee Belongs to</p>
<p>· Deployment Area: Deployment Areas in which the
    Interviewees Had to Perform Forced Labor</p>
<p>· Language: Interview Language</p>
<p>·
  Internment Conditions: Internment
    Conditions of the Interviewees</p>

<p>·
  Place of Residence (Country): Interviewees’ Current
    Country of Residence</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can use the Full Text Search
  option to search the interview holdings of the archive or get started by using the
  <%= link_to (t :collections_map), interview_collections_url, :title => "Collections" %> showing the geographical distribution of the subsets of the
  collection.</p>







